      <ul><li><a href=\"https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2022PhRvD.106d3520P/abstract\" class=\"text-primary\" target=\"_blank\">Dark Energy Survey year 3 results: Constraints on cosmological parameters and galaxy-bias models from galaxy clustering and galaxy-galaxy lensing using the redMaGiC sample</a><br>Pandey, S. ; Krause, E.; et al (2022)&nbsp;</li><li><a href=\"https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2022PhRvD.105b3515S/abstract\" class=\"text-primary\" target=\"_blank\">Dark Energy Survey Year 3 results: Cosmology from cosmic shear and robustness to modeling uncertainty</a><br>Secco, L. F. ; Samuroff, S. ; Krause, E. ; et al (2022)</li><li><a href=\"https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2022PhRvD.105b3520A/abstract\" class=\"text-primary\" target=\"_blank\">Dark Energy Survey Year 3 results: Cosmological constraints from galaxy clustering and weak lensing</a><br>DES collaboration et al (2022)</li><li><a href=\"https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2021arXiv210513548K/abstract\" class=\"text-primary\" target=\"_blank\">Dark Energy Survey Year 3 Results: Multi-Probe Modeling Strategy and Validation</a><br>Krause, E. ; Fang, X.&nbsp; et al (2021)</li><li><a href=\"https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2021MNRAS.502.6010H/abstract\" class=\"text-primary\" target=\"_blank\">Dark energy survey year 1 results: Constraining baryonic physics in the Universe</a><br>Huang, Hung-Jin ; Eifler, Tim et al (2021)</li><li><a href=\"https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2021PhRvL.126n1301T/abstract\" class=\"text-primary\" target=\"_blank\">Dark Energy Survey Year 1 Results: Cosmological Constraints from Cluster Abundances, Weak Lensing, and Galaxy Correlations</a><br>To, C. ; Krause, E. ; Rozo, E. ; Wu, H. ; Gruen, D. ; Wechsler, R. H. ; Eifler, T. F.&nbsp; et al (2021)</li></ul><ul>\n                    </ul>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</section>",
