f=\"https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2022MNRAS.509.5721F/abstract\" class=\"text-primary\" target=\"_blank\">Cosmology from clustering, cosmic shear, CMB lensing, and cross correlations: combining Rubin observatory and Simons Observatory</a><br>Fang, Xiao ; Eifler, Tim ; Schaan, Emmanuel ; Huang, Hung-Jin ; Krause, Elisabeth ; Ferraro, Simone (2022)</li><li><a href=\"https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2020MNRAS.497.2699F/abstract\" class=\"text-primary\" target=\"_blank\">2D-FFTLog: efficient computation of real-space covariance matrices for galaxy clustering and weak lensing</a><br>Fang, Xiao ; Eifler, Tim; Krause, Elisabeth (2020)</li><li><a href=\"https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2019MNRAS.488.1652H/abstract\" class=\"text-primary\" target=\"_blank\">Modelling baryonic physics in future weak lensing surveys</a><br>Huang, Hung-Jin ; Eifler, Tim ; Mandelbaum, Rachel ; Dodelson, Scott</li><li><a href=\"https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2018arXiv180901669T/abstract\" class=\"text-primary\" target=\"_blank\">The LSST Dark Energy Science Collaboration (DESC) Science Requirements Document</a><br>The LSST Dark Energy Science Collaboration ; Mandelbaum, Rachel ; Eifler, Tim&nbsp; et al (2018)</li><li><a href=\"https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2017MNRAS.470.2100K/abstract\" class=\"text-primary\" target=\"_blank\">cosmolike - cosmological likelihood analyses for photometric galaxy surveys</a><br>Krause, Elisabeth ; Eifler, Tim (2017)</li><li><a href=\"https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2017PhRvD..95l3512S/abstract\" class=\"text-primary\" target=\"_blank\">Looking through the same lens: Shear calibration for LSST, Euclid, and WFIRST with stage 4 CMB lensing</a><br>Schaan, Emmanuel ; Krause, Elisabeth ; Eifler, Tim ; Doré, Olivier ; Miyatake, Hironao ; Rhodes, Jason ; Spergel, David N. (2017)</li></ul><ul>\n                    </ul>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</section>",
